The paper discusses a neuromorphic computing system and presents a novel ultra-low leakage cell and an automatic gain control scheme for analog log-domain synapse circuits. The focus is on homeostatic plasticity, which is a mechanism for stabilizing neural activity around a functional operating point. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses circuit design and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.ET (Embedded Systems) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results and measurements, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.EM (Electromagnetics).
